    <text>
        <body>
            <entry xml:id="entry_barz" xml:lang="os">
                <form type="lemma"><orth>barz</orth></form>
                <sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>куча</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>pile</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>возвышение</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>rising ground</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>курган</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>barrow</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense><sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>множество</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>multitude</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense></sense>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>mulʒuguti barz</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>муравьиная куча</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>anthill</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <re>
                    <form type="lemma"><orth>ænæqæn bærztæ</orth></form>
                    <sense><abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>целые громады</q>
                        </abv:tr><abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>whole masses</q>
                        </abv:tr></sense>
                </re>
                <abv:exampleGrp>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>uxstitæ ... mulʒug bærzi nikʼkʼwærdta</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>он воткнул вертелы в муравьиную кучу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>he put spits in the anthill</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mænæ ʽj mulʒug bærzbæl baivardton</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>вот я положил его на муравьиную кучу</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>here I put it on the anthill</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                    </abv:example>
                    <abv:example>
                        <quote>mulʒugi bærzmæ batuxstæj i mard</quote>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="ru">
                            <q>труп очутился на муравьиной куче</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <abv:tr xml:lang="en">
                            <q>a corpse appeared in the anthill</q>
                        </abv:tr>
                        <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II
                            41—42</biblScope></bibl>
                    </abv:example>
                </abv:exampleGrp>
                <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср.<mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>barəzah-</w>
                        <gloss><q>высота</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>гора</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>barəz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>burz</w>
                        <gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>burz</w>
                        <gloss><q>высокий</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>высота</q></gloss></mentioned> , <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>berj</w>
                        <gloss><q>высота</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Berg</w>
                        <gloss><q>гора</q></gloss></mentioned>. Эта же основа налична в слове <ref
                        type="xr" target="#entry_bærzond"/> ‘высокий’, под которым даются дальнейшие
                    соответствия. Из осетинского идет <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>barz</w></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Бартоломей</author></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>bōrz</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_СМК"
                            /><biblScope>XXIX 10</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>boarz</w>
                        <gloss><q>куча</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>курган</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>zungæti boarz</w>
                        <gloss><q>муравьиная куча</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"
                            ><w>Ačmæz boarz</w>
                        <gloss><q>Ачамазов курган</q></gloss></mentioned>).</etym>
                <etym xml:lang="en">Сf. <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/>
                        <w>barəzah-</w>
                        <gloss><q>height</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>гора</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="ae"
                            ><w>barəz-</w>
                        <gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="fa"><lang/>
                        <w>burz</w>
                        <gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><lang/>
                        <w>burz</w>
                        <gloss><q>high</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="pal"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>height</q></gloss></mentioned> , <mentioned xml:lang="xcl"><lang/>
                        <w>berj</w>
                        <gloss><q>height</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="de"><lang/>
                        <w>Berg</w>
                        <gloss><q>mountain</q></gloss></mentioned>. The same stem is found in the
                    word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bærzond"/> ‘high’, where further
                    correspondences are given. The following words come from Ossetic: <mentioned
                        xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>barz</w></mentioned> (<bibl><author>Bartolomei</author></bibl>),
                        <mentioned xml:lang="ce"><lang/>
                        <w>bōrz</w></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_СМК"
                            /><biblScope>XXIX 10</biblScope></bibl>), <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>boarz</w>
                        <gloss><q>pile</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"><w/>
                        <gloss><q>barrow</q></gloss></mentioned> (<mentioned xml:lang="inh"><lang/>
                        <w>zungæti boarz</w>
                        <gloss><q>anthill</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="inh"
                            ><w>Ačmæz boarz</w>
                        <gloss><q>Achamaz barrow</q></gloss></mentioned>).</etym>
            </entry>
        </body>
